or\nmanufacturer, who produces\ndiscovered that the folks who once bought the highest\npriced car had dropped to the lowest-priced car, which, in\ncidcntally, carries a higher price tag than the lop models did\nbefore the profit spree started. Nobody is buying the sky\npriced car.\nBusiness is off, decidedly. Unemployment is much greater\nEven profits have skidded a little.\nthan it was a year ago.\nThere is talk among industrialists of \"stabilization, and\nof washing out the ''weaker'' competitor\nof course, the independents,\nis starting to cry that if Labor, the working people, insist on\nwage increases to meet in some small part the vastly increased\ncost of living, the result will be, not higher prices, but a re\ncession in business.\nLabor caused inflation: Labor is now causing deflation,\nthat is the N.A.M. switch. All of which is utterly fallacious,\nof course, but if the big fellows repeat it often enough and\nif their publicity agencies din it into the public's ears, as\nthey will, undoubtedly a lot of folks are going to believe it\neventually.\nwhich means,\nAt the same time, the N.A.M.\nJOHNSON BAR\nI 57 East Park Street\n;P1NK BEKS, WINE, LIQUORS;\nYonr Favorit\u00ab Mined Drinks\nLLOYD HAMILTON\nACOMA LOUNGE\nButte'a Finest\n33 N. Wyoming\nI\nKXLF PROGRAM SCHEDULE\nwn\nTIME\niDAY 1.1C.HT SAVTNi\n.1 NDAY\nH 00 World V w\n8 15 Sto\n\n30 Cameo of Mu\nPulpit\nNational Rudi\u00ab\ns and.n-r\u00ab >n Melod.e\u00ab-\nFav\nM>ad\u00ab\n9 00\nMorning\nNew< Hi\nLit\u00bb\nng Scientists\nfor Y\nSignposts\n11 oo Living 1949\nli 30 Publi\n11 45 Report on Europe\n12 00- NBC Symphony\nl 00 \u2014V\nAffairs\nthe Wind\ns Dow\nl 30\u2014NBC University Th\nFamily\nitr\u00ab\n2 30 One\nQuo- Kids\n3 3U -Ne\n3 35 Ja\n4 00 RCA Victor Show\n4 10 International Harvester Show\nMetal s Bank Hi Liles of Hi\nMilwaukee Hoad New\nFashloi\nPickens Show\n5\n5,30\n5 45 Emil Marans\n6 00 Rrchafd Diamond\nC 30 Phil Harns-Allce Faye\n7 00 Fred Allen\n7 30 Henry Morgan\n8 00 Walter Wlnchel